# S10-T02: Tone.js Lazy Init

## Objective
Keep the browser console clean on cold load — no AudioContext or Tone.js init until the
first user gesture (Play tap or piano key down).

## Root cause
- `StartScreen` calls `getNoteFinderKeyboardAudioEngine().preload()` on mount.
- `useNoteFinderKeyboardAudio` preloads when `preload: true` (interactive PianoKeyboard).
- `new Sampler()` in preload creates Tone nodes before gesture.

## Acceptance Criteria
- Fresh load → DevTools console: zero Tone/AudioContext warnings.
- First Play click or piano key: audio works (engine loads + `Tone.start()`).
- Assistive StartScreen piano remains silent and does not trigger preload.
- Game feedback (`useAudioFeedback`) still works after first gesture.
- No regression to piano tap latency after preload completes.

## Steps
1. Refactor `noteFinderKeyboardAudioEngine.ts`: defer `new Sampler()` until `ensureReady()` called after `Tone.start()`.
2. Remove `StartScreen` mount-time `preload()` call.
3. Set `PianoKeyboard` default `preload: false`; trigger `ensureReady()` inside `auditionDown` / first game key handler.
4. Wire game `handlePianoKey` to call `ensureReady()` once on first interactive press.
5. Move sample download to post-gesture path; show no console.error unless load fails after gesture.
6. Cold-load verify console; tap Play + key — audio OK.
7. `git commit -m "fix(audio): defer Tone.js init until user gesture"`.
